# Flask Project Structure

## Main Application
The main entry point for the application is [app.py](mdc:app.py), which contains most routes and Flask configuration.

## Models and Database
Database models are defined in [models.py](mdc:models.py).

## Audio Processing
Audio-related functions are handled in:
- [audio_functions.py](mdc:audio_functions.py) - Core audio processing
- [audio_routes.py](mdc:audio_routes.py) - API routes for audio
- [audio_utils.py](mdc:audio_utils.py) - Utility functions

## Templates
The application uses Jinja2 templates organized in the `templates` directory:
- `asistencia/` - Attendance-related templates
- `clases/` - Class management templates
- `horarios/` - Schedule templates
- `profesores/` - Teacher management templates
- `informes/` - Reports templates

## Static Assets
Static files are stored in the `static` directory:
- `audio/` - Audio files
- `css/` - Stylesheets
- `js/` - JavaScript files
- `img/` - Images and icons
- `uploads/` - User uploaded files

## Scripts
Helper scripts are divided by platform:
- `scripts/mac/` - macOS scripts
- `scripts/windows/` - Windows scripts

## Utilities
Various utility functions and scripts:
- [notifications.py](mdc:notifications.py) - Notification system
- [check_notifications.py](mdc:check_notifications.py) - Notification verification
- [export_to_excel.py](mdc:export_to_excel.py) - Excel export functionality
